  note         = {Earliest primary source in the predecessor-systems lineage at DLR ZLP Augsburg. Specifies the automation control concept for the Multifunktionale Fertigungszelle (Multifunctional Production Cell). Read for design intent, it articulates 14 commitments that map directly onto Shepard surfaces a decade-plus later: \textit{Konsequente Vermeidung von Einzel-/Insel-L{\"o}sungen} (avoidance of point/island solutions), \textit{Modulare Architektur f{\"u}r schrittweise Weiterentwicklung} (modular architecture for incremental evolution), \textit{Generische Schnittstelle f{\"u}r Messdatenerfassung} (generic measurement-data interface -- the PayloadKind / PayloadStorage SPI ancestor), \textit{Automatische Dokumentation von Prozessdaten} (automatic process-data documentation -- the W3C-PROV Activity stream ancestor), \textit{Detektion von Abweichungen zum Kalibrier-Prozess} (deviation detection from calibration baseline -- anomaly-detection ancestor), \textit{Zentrale Datenhaltung auf Datenbank} (central DB-backed storage), \textit{Replay-F{\"a}higkeit in Simulation zur Analyse und Optimierung} (replay capability for analysis and optimisation), \textit{Anlagenkonfigurationsmanagement} (plant configuration management -- the admin-configurable knobs ancestor, cf. A3b / N1c2 / UH1a), \textit{Offene Schnittstellen: AutomationML, XML} (open interfaces), \textit{Drahtloses virtuelles SmartPAD} + \textit{Mobile Bedienpanels} (wireless shop-floor terminals), \textit{Integration des NDT Frameworks ($\to$ PI-NDT)} (NDT as first-class). Primary source for \texttt{aidocs/strategy/86-shepard-predecessor-systems.md} \S 1.5 (pre-PRAESTO design thinking already articulated in 2010).},
  category     = {dlr_internal}
}

